The paper deals with the usability and security challenges of Bitcoin key management, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The evaluation framework and usability evaluation conducted in the paper involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) aspects. The paper also discusses the potential for rethinking key management for end-users, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
